  "text": "In this study, initial mold and yeast counts were approximately 2 log CFU/g and reached 6.49-6.95 and 2.03-3.08 log CFU/g in samples stored in air and vacuum packaging, respectively (Fig. 1d ). Lower mold and yeast counts in test samples compared to control indicates the presence of EOs antifungal constituents in meat products [CITATION_1] .",
